PHENOMENAL. I really wish you'd make more cages (maybe some paid add-ons?) so I could play it more! Pleaaaaase! An incredible artistic creation and so politically shrewd (which is important in these times). A fantastic addition to the canon of Orwellian satire. I wish there were more mature mobile games like this and Beholder for us gamers looking to be intellectually challenged. Thank you.

Difficult to describe. One of the most surreal games I've played. It sort of messes with your mind. I have to give it 5* for originality alone. Even though it leaves me with an uneasy feeling. It also has replay value, though if I didn't know that I might have given up after the first play through.
Игра отличная, но нет возможности принудительно авторизоваться в Play Games и нет кнопки «Достижения», поэтому в процессе игры достижения не выполняются. Добавьте возможность, пожалуйста.
Really good game, though to my misfortune had nothing to do with monkeys. Would recommend to anyone who likes a good plot in video games

It's a work of keen, surreal satire. I think some of the cages are red herrings, but the game feels like they might not be. Shoutout to Graystillplays on YouTube! I did run into one freezing bug, though... When you're giving Gus the title of the book for him to print, the game's freezing for me after the second title component. I don't think this prevents completion of the game? But I do think it means you can't close the cage... ? I tried happiness -> sorrow and vice versa.

Great game but EXTREMELY SHORT. If it was longer it would definitely be worth the money but alas, since it is only a solid 1 or 2 hours worth of game play until you officially reach the ending (level 25) - it was most definitely not worth what I paid. Hopefully they will improve upon this, soooo I guess we'll just have to wait and see

Fun and different! Would be even better if the clues weren't highlighted and we had to try to decide which ones were clues. Also the ending is a little disappointing. Was hoping for a boss cage or something like that. But the journey to the end is super fun and the replay value is high.
Just like masked maiden in the game says, it's addicting. Worth the money for it's replay value
The game play is confusing and the monkeys don't do anything interesting so it gets boring real quick
Great game

Brilliant game. I currently give 3 stars, as this will be the 3rd time I have had to re install. Once I have switched off my devise the game fails to load, just showing a blank screen after the delvolopers logos show up. If anyone can help ? that would be great
Love love love this game! Very under rated experience.... Just wish it was a little cheaper

It was a great game overall, I really enjoyed having to juggle both the observations and daily life. I'm sure I haven't even scratched the surface for most of the cages. I am confused though, some of the cages there's literally nothing you can do but watch. I was also hoping the game would last a bit longer than it did, rather than just until you reach the 4th level. It would allow for more observation and more understanding of what's going on within each cage.
this game seems cool but the print is so small you can't read it to figure out what you need to do in the game I want my money I can't read this game

content: It's kinda cool, and difficult. I love the mystery solving stuff and yeah. Too many tasks though but it's a very great game.
Good game , observation is important and well it's a blast
Awesome game

Peeping tom simulator: moral dilemma 101 meets Black Mirror. Very much in the vain of Papers, please!, Independent and Beholder. If the manage-your-life part of the simulation distract you too much, the game propose the option to deal with it automatically: good idea.
Describe my experience ? Amazing. Those of you who hasnt played this game, should.

Love the concept of the game and the resource management is challenging and fun. I love that each cage has it's own story and that it can change depending on how you interact or don't interact with the monkeys. I hope that this game eventually gets a sequel.

I've been in love with this game since Yippee Ki Yay Mr Falcon showcased it a while back, and now being in mobile is awesome! I really hope yous add more and new content to the game because it's still a great game and having an ENDLESS sandbox type mode with new scenarios would really be amazing!! Obviously it would end at some point, but maybe once you get through all the cages! ✌
Love the game. Amazing game on PC and on phone.

A little different than the PC version, but not in a bad way. Game is still great. My only complaint would be that there doesn't seem to be any way to view food stats like on PC. On PC you could hover your mouse over food and a pop-up would tell you which foods fill how much hunger, or how much they affect health. You could hover your mouse over your health, energy, and hunger meters to see their numerical value too. I couldn't find this function in this version.
